          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1650979204649-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>breast portion[s]</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Once golden, add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> to the pan, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1650979209086-x200.jpg",
